opwatch Calculator image"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
          </div>

          <div class=3D"content-area">
<p style=3D"text-align:center">
<a href=3D"https://www.natavision.com/calculator.html">Start Stopwatch Calc=
ulator</a>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p>A calculator for stopwatch arithmetic. Add, subtract, multiply, and divi=
de race times without converting to seconds. Perfect for swimming and runni=
ng / track / cross county. Intended for coaches, parents, and athletes.</p>

<p>Times are in HH:mm:ss.hh format (hours, minutes, seconds, hundredths). T=
here is no need to type the colon or period, so "12345" is interpreted as "=
1:23.45" and ":30" is interpreted as "30.00".</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b></p>
<p>
</p><ol>
<li><b>Calculating splits.</b> Leg 4 started at 3:14.67 and ended at 4:11.5=
0. What was leg 4's split?<br><br>
    4 1 1 5 0 - 3 1 4 6 7 =3D 56.83<p></p></li>
<li><b>Calculating pace.</b> Runner A finished the marathon in 3:26:54.48. =
What was her mile pace?<br><br>
    3 2 6 5 4 4 8 =C3=B7 2 6 . 2 =3D 7:53.83<p></p></li>
<li><b>Calculating set duration.</b> How long will 20 50s on :55 take to sw=
im in practice?<br><br>
    : 5 5 =C3=97 2 0 =3D 18:20.00<p></p></li>
<li><b>Calculating relay seed times.</b> The four runners' individual times=
 are 54.68, 57.32, 57.98, and 1:00.04. What would their relay time be?<br><=
br>
    5 4 6 8 + 5 7 3 2 + 5 7 9 8 + 1 0 0 0 4 =3D 3:50.02<p></p></li>
<li><b>Converting between courses.</b> Swimmer A swam a 5:44.86 short cours=
e yards 400 IM. What is that in meters? (1 yard =3D 0.9144 meters)<br><br>
    5 4 4 8 6 =C3=97 . 9 1 4 4 =3D 5:15.33<p></p></li>
</ol>
<br>
Runs in the browser. Available for free.
<p></p>
<p style=3D"text-align:center">
